related_questions.question: How much do Railroad conductors make?
related_questions.snippet: In May 2017, railroad conductors received a median salary of $60,300; earnings for the lower half of conductors fell below this amount, and earnings for the top half were above it. The bottom 10 percent of conductors made below $42,950 annually, while the top 10 percent earned high salaries over $91,630.Sep 24, 2018
